      "content": "# Poster Concepts: Dune: Part One\n\n## About This Document\nThese are key-art directions for a campaign designer. Each concept should read at thumbnail size and stay attached to specific script evidence.\n\n---\n\n## Category: Character-Driven\n\n**Concept 1: PAUL Against the System**\n- **Style:** Monumental character one-sheet\n- **Composition:** PAUL small against caladan castle, with the key visual pressure from the opening movement.\n- **Color Palette:** #C88935 (Weathered Ochre), #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black), #D9D0BC (Bone White)\n- **Typography:** Tall, restrained serif title with wide-set sans-serif credits.\n- **Tagline:** \"Inheritance is a hostile world.\"\n- **Mood:** Propulsive, isolated, immense\n- **Campaign Read:** large-scale genre and design-forward audiences\n- **AI Prompt:** Restrained genre poster for Dune: Part One, PAUL against caladan castle, bleak epic sci-fi, visible details only from the supplied screenplay JSON, no invented characters or plot events.\n\n**Concept 2: The System in Formation**\n- **Style:** Formal ensemble poster\n- **Composition:** PAUL, JESSICA, LETO, DUNCAN arranged by allegiance, threat, and scale, with caladan castle implied behind them.\n- **Color Palette:** #C88935 (Weathered Ochre), #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black), #D9D0BC (Bone White), #4A4642 (Smoke Gray)\n- **Typography:** Architectural, quiet, and ceremonial.\n- **Tagline:** \"The future arrives armed.\"\n- **Mood:** Formal, tense, inevitable\n- **Campaign Read:** large-scale genre and design-forward audiences\n- **AI Prompt:** Ensemble key art for Dune: Part One, formal arrangement of the major characters named in the JSON, caladan castle, controlled color, bleak epic sci-fi, no unrelated genre details.\n\n## Category: Symbolic / Metaphorical\n\n**Concept 3: The Myth Object**\n- **Style:** Symbolic object poster\n- **Composition:** crysknife isolated at large scale as a practical object with mythic consequence.\n- **Color Palette:** #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black), #D9D0BC (Bone White)\n- **Typography:** Small title, lots of negative space, no decorative texture unless tied to the object.\n- **Tagline:** \"Small objects carry large worlds.\"\n- **Mood:** Ritual, precise, ominous\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who respond to iconic production objects.\n- **AI Prompt:** Minimalist poster for Dune: Part One, crysknife isolated with dramatic practical importance, restrained negative space, no unrelated props.\n\n**Concept 4: The World as Pressure**\n- **Style:** Environmental metaphor poster\n- **Composition:** Caladan Castle becomes the campaign image, with one small figure or object showing the world's scale.\n- **Color Palette:** #C88935 (Weathered Ochre), #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black), #D9D0BC (Bone White), #4A4642 (Smoke Gray)\n- **Typography:** Title embedded low in the environment so scale reads first.\n- **Tagline:** \"Power has a landscape.\"\n- **Mood:** Immense, quiet, fatalistic\n- **Campaign Read:** large-scale genre and design-forward audiences\n- **AI Prompt:** Environmental one-sheet for Dune: Part One, caladan castle becomes the campaign image, with one small figure or object showing the world's scale. Graphic readability at thumbnail size, no invented geography.\n\n## Category: Scene-Based\n\n**Concept 5: Scene 10 Signal**\n- **Style:** Scene-led campaign image\n- **Composition:** Paul trembles in agony with his hand in the dark box while the gom jabbar rests against his neck.\n- **Color Palette:** #C88935 (Weathered Ochre), #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black)\n- **Typography:** Title clear at thumbnail size, secondary copy minimal.\n- **Tagline:** \"Scale has teeth.\"\n- **Mood:** Extreme Tension And Survival\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who want one memorable scripted moment as the campaign hook.\n- **AI Prompt:** Key art for Dune: Part One, Scene 10: Paul trembles in agony with his hand in the dark box while the gom jabbar rests against his neck. Keep only characters and objects named in the script data, no extra plot details.\n\n**Concept 6: Scene 5 Signal**\n- **Style:** Scene-led campaign image\n- **Composition:** Paul describes his prophetic dreams to Duncan amid military prep.\n- **Color Palette:** #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black), #D9D0BC (Bone White)\n- **Typography:** Title clear at thumbnail size, secondary copy minimal.\n- **Tagline:** \"Ritual turns into survival.\"\n- **Mood:** Camaraderie And Foreshadowing\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who want one memorable scripted moment as the campaign hook.\n- **AI Prompt:** Key art for Dune: Part One, Scene 5: Paul describes his prophetic dreams to Duncan amid military prep. Keep only characters and objects named in the script data, no extra plot details.\n\n**Concept 7: Scene 16 Signal**\n- **Style:** Scene-led campaign image\n- **Composition:** Paul successfully uses the Voice to force the trooper to cut Jessica's bonds, initiating a bloody struggle in the airborne craft.\n- **Color Palette:** #111513 (Ceremonial Black), #D9D0BC (Bone White), #4A4642 (Smoke Gray)\n- **Typography:** Title clear at thumbnail size, secondary copy minimal.\n- **Tagline:** \"No inheritance is clean.\"\n- **Mood:** Survival And Awakening Power\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers who want one memorable scripted moment as the campaign hook.\n- **AI Prompt:** Key art for Dune: Part One, Scene 16: Paul successfully uses the Voice to force the trooper to cut Jessica's bonds, initiating a bloody struggle in the airborne craft. Keep only characters and objects named in the script data, no extra plot details.\n\n## Category: Minimalist / Typographic\n\n**Concept 8: The Title as Terrain**\n- **Style:** Typographic conceptual poster\n- **Composition:** The title treated like a physical system from the screenplay, with one figure or object moving through the letterforms.\n- **Color Palette:** #C88935 (Weathered Ochre), #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black)\n- **Typography:** Massive serif or chiseled sans-serif, quiet spacing, no distressed effects.\n- **Tagline:** \"A world inside a name.\"\n- **Mood:** Iconic, austere, memorable\n- **Campaign Read:** large-scale genre and design-forward audiences.\n- **AI Prompt:** Minimal typographic poster for Dune: Part One, title as a physical system tied to the screenplay, one small character silhouette or hero object from the JSON, controlled palette, no unrelated genre language.\n\n**Concept 9: The Production Map**\n- **Style:** Production-design one-sheet\n- **Composition:** A restrained map of caladan castle, arrakeen residency, arrakis desert, with one object or event marker per location.\n- **Color Palette:** #C88935 (Weathered Ochre), #3D4652 (Slate Blue), #111513 (Ceremonial Black), #D9D0BC (Bone White), #4A4642 (Smoke Gray)\n- **Typography:** Information-design clarity with cinematic restraint.\n- **Tagline:** \"Every place has a cost.\"\n- **Mood:** Designed, strategic, expansive\n- **Campaign Read:** Viewers interested in production design and story structure.\n- **AI Prompt:** Elegant production-map poster for Dune: Part One, restrained map of the script's major locations with small object or event markers from the JSON, no invented geography.",
